    "One example of a more specific funding call comes from the US NIH, which plans to disburse $4.8m in 2025 for the development of ML/AI Tools to Advance Genomic Translational Research (MAGen), foot_26 but this is limited to the analysis of human pathogenic genetic variants and so is less relevant for our capabilities of interest.",
    "Private and venture capital funding is strong and may be more impactful than government funding at the frontier of some capabilities, but is concentrated in some areas.",
    "For instance, the Arc Institute, which developed Evo 2, has over $650m in committed funding, an unknown proportion of which will be dedicated to AI development.",
    "116 Have there been interventions to increase growth or development of these tools, such as commercialization or scaling up of labs?",
    "3 Yes, there are major interventions that are likely to substantially increase growth or tool development."
